quran[30]{c,v,t,f}:
  68,49,"If not that a favor [i.e., mercy] from his Lord overtook him, he would have been thrown onto the naked shore while he was censured.{1}",footnotes:1:[But instead, Allāh accepted his repentance and provided means for his recovery.  See 37:139-148.]
  68,50,"And his Lord chose him and made him of the righteous."
  68,51,"And indeed, those who disbelieve would almost make you slip with their eyes [i.e., looks] when they hear the message, and they say, "
  69,46,"Then We would have cut from him the aorta.{1}",footnotes:1:[Causing immediate death.]
  69,47,"And there is no one of you who could prevent [Us] from him."
  69,48,"And indeed, it [i.e., the Qur’ān] is a reminder for the righteous."
  70,40,"So I swear by the Lord of [all] risings and settings{1} that indeed We are able",footnotes:1:[i.e., Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā), who determines the point at which the sun, moon and stars rise and set according to season and every position of observation.]
  70,41,"To replace them with better than them; and We are not to be outdone."
  70,42,"So leave them to converse vainly and amuse themselves until they meet their Day which they are promised -"
  74,25,"This is not but the word of a human being."
  74,26,"I will drive him into Saqar.{1}",footnotes:1:[One of the proper names of Hell.]
  74,27,"And what can make you know what is Saqar?"
  75,22,"[Some] faces, that Day, will be radiant,"
  75,23,"Looking at their Lord.{1}",footnotes:1:[The people of Paradise will actually see their Creator in the Hereafter.]
  75,24,"And [some] faces, that Day, will be contorted,"
  76,16,"Clear glasses [made] from silver of which they have determined the measure."
  76,17,"And they will be given to drink a cup [of wine] whose mixture is of ginger"
  76,18,"[From] a fountain within it [i.e., Paradise] named Salsabeel."
  77,13,"For the Day of Judgement."
  77,14,"And what can make you know what is the Day of Judgement?"
  77,15,"Woe,{1} that Day, to the deniers.",footnotes:1:[i.e., death and destruction.]
  78,10,"And made the night as clothing{1}.",footnotes:1:[Covering you in darkness and providing rest.]
  78,11,"And made the day for livelihood."
  78,12,"And constructed above you seven strong [heavens]."
  79,4,"And those who race each other in a race{1}",footnotes:1:[Racing to deliver the souls of the believers to Paradise.]
  79,5,"And those who arrange [each] matter,{1}",footnotes:1:[According to Allāh's decree.]
  79,6,"On the Day the blast [of the Horn] will convulse [creation],"
  80,1,"He [i.e., the Prophet (ﷺ) ] frowned and turned away"
  80,2,"Because there came to him the blind man,{1} [interrupting].",footnotes:1:[ʿAbdullāh, the son of Umm Maktūm.]
  80,3,"But what would make you perceive, [O Muḥammad], that perhaps he might be purified{1}",footnotes:1:[As a result of what he learns from you.]
